DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: Capable of life or normal growth and development._Hematopoietic progenitor cell antigen CD34 (385 aa, 41 kD) is a cell motility process protein that is encoded by the human CD34 gene and has a role in cell-cell adhesion and may have a role in leukocyte migration._Being or existing in a specified place or at the specified time._The smallest units of living structure capable of independent existence, composed of a membrane-enclosed mass of protoplasm and containing a nucleus or nucleoid._Any procedure that involves testing or manipulating a sample of blood, urine, or other body substance in a laboratory setting.[manually curated]
